WEBVTT

00:02.500 --> 00:03.100
Previously on

00:03.100 --> 00:03.433
Previously on
"Below Deck"...

00:04.533 --> 00:06.033
- I'm very relaxed
running the deck.

00:06.066 --> 00:07.166
I don't like to micromanage,

00:07.200 --> 00:08.533
and I don't like any hierarchy.

00:10.033 --> 00:11.467
- Have you had--
you've never--

00:11.500 --> 00:13.000
Really?
- Mm-hmm.

00:13.033 --> 00:14.367
Let it go.
This one, Chandler.

00:14.400 --> 00:17.367
Does it go ball first on bow
and then the--

00:17.400 --> 00:19.567
- I really don't have time to
walk Rhylee through the setup.

00:19.600 --> 00:22.133
- I just feel like--
like you could snap.

00:22.166 --> 00:24.467
- [laughs]
- It's not a bad thing.

00:24.500 --> 00:26.500
- That I could snap?
Yeah, that's a bad thing.

00:26.533 --> 00:29.133
I have a very complicated
relationship with my parents.

00:29.166 --> 00:31.100
I grew up in
a very toxic household.

00:31.133 --> 00:33.333
- Us three are gonna go over.
- What would you have me on?

00:33.367 --> 00:34.600
- Someone needs
to stay on here.

00:34.633 --> 00:37.200
- In Alaska, I'm a captain.
I'm not stupid.

00:37.233 --> 00:38.500
You can tell me one thing

00:38.533 --> 00:40.233
and I should be able
to do it just fine.

00:40.266 --> 00:41.600
- Remember the rules:

00:41.633 --> 00:44.066
don't embarrass yourself,
don't embarrass the boat.

00:51.433 --> 00:53.100
- We're just starting
to have a good time.

00:53.133 --> 00:54.600
What's going on?
- No ----ing excuses tomorrow.

00:54.633 --> 00:56.400
6:00 on deck.

00:56.433 --> 00:58.433
- You're pissing everybody else
off for ----ing--

00:58.467 --> 01:00.166
- Stop talking right now.

01:00.200 --> 01:01.667
I will not put up
with this kind of disrespect.

01:01.700 --> 01:04.333
You just straight up
lost your sh--.

01:04.367 --> 01:07.166
- Sorry to speak while
you're ----ing interrupting.

01:08.467 --> 01:09.600
[air horn blows]

01:09.633 --> 01:12.600
[upbeat music]

01:12.633 --> 01:19.633
♪ ♪

01:27.433 --> 01:29.533
- Listen here.
Chandler's your boss.

01:29.567 --> 01:31.233
- You weren't in the van
when he told me

01:31.266 --> 01:32.367
he wasn't my boss at that time

01:32.400 --> 01:34.166
and I could speak
to him freely.

01:34.200 --> 01:35.600
So understand that.
- What happened in the cab?

01:35.633 --> 01:37.433
'Cause I'm Team Chandler,
so what happened?

01:37.467 --> 01:39.133
- I have been on
Team Chandler all along,

01:39.166 --> 01:40.600
until about 30 minutes ago.

01:40.633 --> 01:42.333
- Well, what happened
in the cab?

01:42.367 --> 01:44.066
- I said,
"May I speak freely?"

01:44.100 --> 01:46.233
And I said,
"Well, in my opinion,

01:46.266 --> 01:48.400
"if you make us all
get up at 6:00,

01:48.433 --> 01:51.467
then you're gonna
piss the deck crew off."

01:51.500 --> 01:53.300
And then he said...
- Yeah, duh.

01:53.333 --> 01:55.200
- "Stop ----ing talking to me."

01:55.233 --> 01:57.066
And I said, "Okay,
are you saying that to me

01:57.100 --> 01:58.667
as a boss or as a friend?"
- Both.

01:58.700 --> 02:01.133
- That's what he said.
- He was right.

02:01.166 --> 02:04.400
- I said I will do whatever it
is he requires of us...

02:05.633 --> 02:09.166
and then he stormed out
of the van.

02:09.200 --> 02:11.200
- I understand why
she's frustrated,

02:11.233 --> 02:13.600
but Rhylee just needs to shut
the (BLEEP) up, stop talking.

02:13.633 --> 02:15.233
She needs to know her place.

02:15.266 --> 02:16.667
- You seemed upset
about it earlier.

02:16.700 --> 02:19.233
- Well, I'm upset with the way
that it went down

02:19.266 --> 02:22.367
because I feel like I was
disrespected by Chandler.

02:22.400 --> 02:24.667
- You just straight up
lost your sh--.

02:24.700 --> 02:26.233
- [scoffs]

02:26.266 --> 02:27.567
- I'm just telling you
right now, we're--

02:27.600 --> 02:29.200
- I got it!
I'm--

02:29.233 --> 02:31.400
I said to you
in the ----ing van,

02:31.433 --> 02:33.233
and I said it
just five minutes ago,

02:33.266 --> 02:35.266
I will do what
you've asked me to do.

02:35.300 --> 02:38.433
Sorry to speak while
you're ----ing interrupting.

02:38.467 --> 02:40.367
- I don't know
who Rhylee thinks she is.

02:40.400 --> 02:43.700
I have never dealt with
this kind of disrespect before.

02:43.734 --> 02:46.734
I'm done.
- Good night, Chandler.

02:46.767 --> 02:48.500
- Yeah, I'm gonna
----ing blow up

02:48.533 --> 02:50.667
if I'm being ----ing spoken
to like a (BLEEP).

02:50.700 --> 02:53.500
Maybe I'm just misunderstanding
the whole way...

02:53.533 --> 02:55.633
- Point.
- He asked--

02:55.667 --> 02:57.700
- I understand
what happened,

02:57.734 --> 03:00.367
but now you are
the only person here

03:00.400 --> 03:02.433
raising your voice,
and if I were you,

03:02.467 --> 03:04.200
I would go to sleep.

03:04.233 --> 03:06.700
'Cause you have to be on deck
at 6:00 am.

03:06.734 --> 03:08.734
- I'm gonna do whatever
the (BLEEP) I'm gonna do.

03:08.767 --> 03:11.667
I can say whatever the (BLEEP)
I want to say.

03:11.700 --> 03:14.233
- So then it's okay to speak
to people disrespectfully?

03:14.266 --> 03:15.500
I'm confused.
- Are you?

03:15.533 --> 03:17.300
Or are you just being
condescending?

03:17.333 --> 03:18.667
- Just don't dig a hole deeper.
I would just stop.

03:18.700 --> 03:20.333
I think Rhylee's
a little bit confused.

03:20.367 --> 03:22.200
She has
no yachting experience,

03:22.233 --> 03:24.700
and she needs to respect
everyone else above her.

03:24.734 --> 03:27.467
And everyone else is
above her.

03:29.500 --> 03:31.300
- I'm good.
I don't give a (BLEEP).

03:31.333 --> 03:33.433
- Was that too much?
- Kate, you're never too much.

03:41.734 --> 03:43.400
- It's just alcohol, bro.

03:45.200 --> 03:47.000
- What is Chandler
pissed off about?

03:47.033 --> 03:49.266
- All I know is that you've
gotta get your ----ing ass up

03:49.300 --> 03:50.333
at 5:45.

03:51.333 --> 03:53.000
- How are you feeling?

03:53.033 --> 03:54.734
- [sighs]

03:54.767 --> 03:57.333
Some bosun.

03:57.367 --> 03:59.667
- I'll see you in a second.
Hopefully you're asleep.

03:59.700 --> 04:02.166
♪ ♪

04:02.200 --> 04:04.200
- This is bullsh--.

04:08.300 --> 04:11.200
[upbeat music]

04:11.233 --> 04:13.300
[alarm buzzes]

04:13.333 --> 04:15.500
♪ ♪

04:20.333 --> 04:22.233
- (BLEEP)

04:22.266 --> 04:24.467
- I can go on no sleep
and still do my ----ing job.

04:24.500 --> 04:25.767
I do it all summer long.

04:26.000 --> 04:27.400
It's not gonna affect me.

04:27.433 --> 04:31.200
♪ ♪

04:34.000 --> 04:36.433
- Good morning, cuzzy.
How are you?

04:36.467 --> 04:38.200
So where did we start and where
did we finish yesterday?

04:46.333 --> 04:50.266
It was like an hour and a half
of everyone waiting for you.

04:51.567 --> 04:53.700
Then she got out of hand.

04:53.734 --> 04:57.433
I'm glad she woke up and got
to work like a professional,

04:57.467 --> 05:00.066
but she dug herself into
a deep hole last night

05:00.100 --> 05:02.000
and she's yet
to crawl out of it.

05:02.033 --> 05:04.367
We're gonna have
a serious conversation.

05:04.400 --> 05:06.066
- Okay.

05:06.100 --> 05:09.333
[lively music]

05:09.367 --> 05:15.367
♪ ♪

05:19.033 --> 05:23.266
♪ ♪

05:24.066 --> 05:25.633
- [groans]

05:25.667 --> 05:28.734
[somber music]

05:28.767 --> 05:32.367
I got an email
from my mother this morning

05:32.400 --> 05:35.600
and she's going through
early-onset dementia.

05:35.633 --> 05:37.333
I've struggled with it,

05:37.367 --> 05:39.300
especially because
she's in denial about it.

05:39.333 --> 05:42.734
♪ ♪

05:42.767 --> 05:44.734
Just hearing from her,

05:44.767 --> 05:49.400
it just puts me back in this
very dark, sad place.

05:49.433 --> 05:50.767
♪ ♪

05:51.000 --> 05:52.600
It's heartbreaking really.

05:52.633 --> 05:54.633
It's heartbreaking.

05:54.667 --> 05:58.500
So if you just rinse it,
I'll come behind and dry.

06:02.633 --> 06:05.600
[upbeat music]

06:05.633 --> 06:12.667
♪ ♪

06:18.700 --> 06:19.767
- [laughs]

06:22.066 --> 06:23.066
- Yeah.

06:24.567 --> 06:26.700
- I will never punish
anybody that way.

06:26.734 --> 06:28.400
- [laughs]

06:39.133 --> 06:41.500
- I regret speaking to Kate
the way I did.

06:41.533 --> 06:43.000
I know I have a temper,

06:43.033 --> 06:45.400
but Chandler not
talking to me today,

06:45.433 --> 06:47.433
I think he's a prick.

06:47.467 --> 06:49.767
- Can you just keep pissing
people off more than I do,

06:50.000 --> 06:51.467
so that the attention's
on you...

06:51.500 --> 06:53.166
- No, no.
- Not on me. [chuckles]

06:53.200 --> 06:55.433
♪ ♪

06:55.467 --> 06:57.500
- [humming]

06:57.533 --> 07:00.467
Peanut butter chocolate
something.

07:00.500 --> 07:01.667
- Do you know what time
they started?

07:01.700 --> 07:04.000
- I think 6:00.
- 6:00.

07:04.033 --> 07:05.433
That was a punishment.

07:05.467 --> 07:07.433
- Okay,
who ----ed up?

07:07.467 --> 07:12.100
- Well, Rhylee, rank doesn't
have a lot of value to her.

07:12.133 --> 07:13.767
- It will.
- It should.

07:14.000 --> 07:17.100
[laughter]

07:17.133 --> 07:20.433
[upbeat music]

07:20.467 --> 07:22.333
♪ ♪

07:22.367 --> 07:24.066
- Let me know if you're okay
with the Jacuzzi as is

07:24.100 --> 07:25.700
or if you want me to put a
little more elbow grease

07:25.734 --> 07:28.567
into it for now.
- It's fine for now.

07:30.734 --> 07:32.367
- Kate, Chandler, Adrian,

07:32.400 --> 07:35.000
can I get you guys
up to the wheelhouse

07:35.033 --> 07:37.000
for a preference sheet meeting,
please?

07:37.033 --> 07:38.567
- Copy.
- Morning.

07:38.600 --> 07:40.200
- Morning, Chandler.

07:40.233 --> 07:42.700
- Morning.
- Adrian.

07:42.734 --> 07:45.166
Here's what we have
coming up.

07:45.200 --> 07:47.533
Co-primaries,
Alan and Danielle.

07:47.567 --> 07:49.433
- Yay!
I love them.

07:49.467 --> 07:52.433
Alan and Danielle are, like,
the loveliest charter guests

07:52.467 --> 07:54.133
I've ever had,
and unfortunately,

07:54.166 --> 07:55.600
they had
the worst luck ever.

07:55.633 --> 07:58.533
- We are without a chef.
He's packing now.

07:58.567 --> 07:59.767
- Our chef quit.

08:00.000 --> 08:01.700
What's in there?
- Grenadine, full French.

08:01.734 --> 08:04.500
- Ooh, it's gonna taste amazing!
They're gonna love it!

08:04.533 --> 08:06.667
- Our stewardess, she put
grenadine in their oysters.

08:06.700 --> 08:08.100
- [retches]

08:09.500 --> 08:11.033
- Wait, what?

08:11.066 --> 08:13.066
- These people deserve
the perfect charter.

08:13.100 --> 08:14.567
- 53rd birthday for Alan,

08:14.600 --> 08:16.200
which is first day
of the charter,

08:16.233 --> 08:19.133
and they got engaged
four days ago.

08:19.166 --> 08:21.700
When they get on board tomorrow,
we'll get off the dock

08:21.734 --> 08:25.467
as soon as we can and give them
long massages on the way down,

08:25.500 --> 08:29.100
and then we're taking them
to this natural cave

08:29.133 --> 08:30.567
that's really cool.

08:30.600 --> 08:32.433
Alan wants impeccable service,

08:32.467 --> 08:34.233
midnight pajama party,

08:34.266 --> 08:37.166
Polynesian luau
dinner celebration on the beach.

08:37.200 --> 08:39.166
- Should be fun for them.

08:39.200 --> 08:41.000
- [laughs]
For them.

08:41.033 --> 08:42.433
- We've got a lot to do
before tomorrow.

08:42.467 --> 08:44.033
- Oh, gosh.

08:44.066 --> 08:47.033
[upbeat music]

08:47.066 --> 08:50.767
♪ ♪

08:51.000 --> 08:52.200
- Gonna grab
some lunch.

08:56.667 --> 08:59.200
- Is it hard to plan
for guests in advance?

08:59.233 --> 09:01.033
- Extremely hard.

09:01.066 --> 09:03.467
- So you just order what you
think is probably gonna come up?

09:03.500 --> 09:06.200
- So I use my third eye.
I, like, meditate on it.

09:06.233 --> 09:07.567
- Oh, yeah?
- And I'm like,

09:07.600 --> 09:09.567
"Allergic to fish."
Okay.

09:09.600 --> 09:12.266
- [laughs]
- Lots of fruit.

09:12.300 --> 09:13.633
Then I--and it
always works out.

09:13.667 --> 09:15.433
I order exactly
what they want.

09:15.467 --> 09:17.467
It's incredible.
Like, I don't know how I do it.

09:17.500 --> 09:18.734
- Whatever you're doing,
keep doing it.

09:18.767 --> 09:21.533
It's working well for us.
[both laugh]

09:25.233 --> 09:27.600
- Is this--

09:27.633 --> 09:28.767
what is this?
- I'm just folding it.

09:29.000 --> 09:31.567
It's a queen.
- Oh, okay, cool.

09:31.600 --> 09:34.233
So are you excited
for charter two?

09:34.266 --> 09:37.033
- Super stoked.
[chuckles]

09:38.567 --> 09:40.533
- What's going on?

09:40.567 --> 09:43.567
- [hyperventilating]

09:44.767 --> 09:47.633
- Sorry.
[sniffles]

09:47.667 --> 09:49.567
[dramatic music]

09:49.600 --> 09:50.600
- What the hell?

09:50.633 --> 09:53.600
- [sniffs, breathes heavily]

09:53.633 --> 09:55.500
- Will you go talk to her?

09:55.533 --> 09:57.033
♪ ♪

09:57.066 --> 09:58.600
- Caroline?

10:02.100 --> 10:04.266
- [sniffs, breathes heavily]

10:04.300 --> 10:09.200
♪ ♪

10:10.533 --> 10:14.033
- I am not sure where
I spoke to you disrespectfully.

10:14.066 --> 10:17.133
- You don't have to like me,
but you will respect me.

10:20.433 --> 10:21.033
- [hyperventilating]

10:21.033 --> 10:23.367
- [hyperventilating]
- Caroline?

10:26.734 --> 10:28.233
- Are you okay?
- Uh-huh.

10:28.266 --> 10:29.400
Just give me
one second, okay?

10:29.433 --> 10:30.767
- Are you sure.
- Uh-huh!

10:31.000 --> 10:32.166
Thank you.

10:32.200 --> 10:33.667
- Shall--shall I meet you
in the master?

10:33.700 --> 10:34.767
- Yeah, I'll be right there.
- You sure?

10:35.000 --> 10:35.767
- Uh-huh, yeah.
- Okay.

10:36.000 --> 10:38.300
- Thank you.

10:38.333 --> 10:41.133
I worry about my mom.

10:41.166 --> 10:43.000
[sniffs]

10:43.033 --> 10:46.400
It's really hard to see
somebody lose their mind.

10:46.433 --> 10:48.266
I can only control
what I can control,

10:48.300 --> 10:50.300
and I can't control this.

10:50.333 --> 10:51.734
You just feel helpless.

10:51.767 --> 10:54.200
[dramatic music]

10:54.233 --> 10:56.300
[groans]

10:56.333 --> 10:57.667
- Are you okay?
- Yeah.

10:57.700 --> 10:59.600
I just had
a little rough patch.

10:59.633 --> 11:02.000
This is home--like, stuff at
home, it's nothing on the boat.

11:02.033 --> 11:03.033
- Okay.

11:06.500 --> 11:08.233
- Is she sick?

11:08.266 --> 11:10.633
- She's starting to go through
early-onset dementia.

11:15.367 --> 11:17.166
- No. I'm just
so sorry for you.

11:17.200 --> 11:19.467
- Do you mind if I take--
take five, and then I'm--

11:19.500 --> 11:21.033
- No.
- Okay.

11:21.066 --> 11:22.300
- Go cool off.
- Okay, thanks.

11:22.333 --> 11:23.700
Sorry. I'm sorry.
- Don't be sorry.

11:23.734 --> 11:25.166
- Okay.

11:26.367 --> 11:28.033
- I hope she's okay.

11:28.066 --> 11:30.633
Being on a yacht is like
being in a weird family.

11:30.667 --> 11:32.200
Yes, there's
a lot of work to do,

11:32.233 --> 11:34.133
but if someone's upset
about something,

11:34.166 --> 11:35.734
you have to be there
for them.

11:35.767 --> 11:38.367
♪ ♪

11:40.767 --> 11:44.066
- Baby, so nice
to hear your voice.

11:44.100 --> 11:47.467
It's good.
It's pretty hectic.

11:47.500 --> 11:49.233
I'm in an open relationship
with my girlfriend.

11:49.266 --> 11:50.467
You know,
I'm not ready to commit

11:50.500 --> 11:52.233
for a lifelong relationship.

11:52.266 --> 11:54.734
I'm very passionate about life
and all its forms.

11:54.767 --> 11:58.100
I love the pleasures
of the flesh, as you would say.

11:58.133 --> 12:01.033
I miss you so much.
I think about you all the time.

12:01.066 --> 12:05.233
Felicia, my girlfriend, has
a lot of the same views as me.

12:05.266 --> 12:07.200
Baby, I want to cuddle.

12:07.233 --> 12:09.266
She's just so calm
and stress-free,

12:09.300 --> 12:11.100
and that's what I need
in my life right now,

12:11.133 --> 12:13.066
especially with all
the hecticness that's going on,

12:13.100 --> 12:15.100
like all that aggressivity
last night.

12:15.133 --> 12:17.266
Okay, sweet angel, well,
I'll try and call you back.

12:17.300 --> 12:18.767
I love you.
Take care.

12:19.000 --> 12:21.400
- [sighs]

12:21.433 --> 12:24.133
I'm ----ing tired, bro.

12:24.166 --> 12:27.033
- Deck crew, deck crew,
you can knock off.

12:27.066 --> 12:29.100
- Copy.

12:29.133 --> 12:31.533
[upbeat music]

12:31.567 --> 12:33.767
- Just can't believe
the views here.

12:34.000 --> 12:36.367
♪ ♪

12:39.433 --> 12:40.734
[dramatic music]

12:40.767 --> 12:42.266
- Hey, you have a second?

12:42.300 --> 12:44.233
- Yeah.
- Let's go.

12:44.266 --> 12:47.700
Obviously, I need to have
a conversation with Rhylee.

12:47.734 --> 12:52.066
I just physically do not have
the mental capacity

12:52.100 --> 12:54.367
to deal with whatever the hell
is gonna come out of her mouth.

12:54.400 --> 12:56.200
I'm gonna keep this
short and sweet.

12:56.233 --> 12:59.100
Last night, I think
some things were said that

12:59.133 --> 13:01.333
both of us probably regret.

13:01.367 --> 13:05.000
You know, I did not handle
that situation

13:05.033 --> 13:06.400
as well as I should have.

13:06.433 --> 13:08.100
So I apologize for that.

13:08.133 --> 13:10.200
We're good.

13:10.233 --> 13:14.100
But if anything happens like
that again, the disrespect,

13:14.133 --> 13:17.033
I mean, would you talk
to Captain like that?

13:17.066 --> 13:19.300
- I'm confused, 'cause when
you told me to shut up,

13:19.333 --> 13:21.333
I shut up.

13:21.367 --> 13:23.233
- And then it carried
on in the crew mess

13:23.266 --> 13:25.266
for another hour and a half.
- I am not sure

13:25.300 --> 13:29.033
where I spoke to you
disrespectfully.

13:29.066 --> 13:30.500
- I don't have time for
this petty stuff on the side.

13:30.533 --> 13:32.200
I'm here to work.

13:32.233 --> 13:35.200
You don't have to like me,
but you will respect me.

13:35.233 --> 13:36.367
Right?

13:36.400 --> 13:38.066
- Yes, sir.

13:38.100 --> 13:40.500
- Okay, we'll leave it at that.
- Okay.

13:40.533 --> 13:42.400
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

13:42.433 --> 13:44.133
♪ ♪

13:44.166 --> 13:46.200
I work on boats.
I'm a captain.

13:46.233 --> 13:49.233
So I absolutely feel like
I deserve respect, you know.

13:49.266 --> 13:51.266
If you disrespect me,
I'm not gonna respect you.

13:51.300 --> 13:53.600
You're not gonna demand respect
from me, you're gonna earn it.

13:53.633 --> 13:55.533
I don't know what to do.

13:55.567 --> 13:58.467
[upbeat music]

13:58.500 --> 14:00.100
♪ ♪

14:00.133 --> 14:02.166
- The entire beer, brother.
